		</dt>
		<dd class="lead">A Canadian navy intelligence officer charged with communicating information to a foreign entity or terrorist group has agreed to stay in custody for now and not make a bail application, his lawyer says.  <a href="/news/politics/story/2012/01/17/ns-security-charges-halifax-hearing.html" class="more">more <span>&raquo;</span></a></dd>
		
